# Text Component Styling

When using the `Text` component from `@/components/text`, always prefer the `color` and `variant` props over using the `style` prop for color and typography.

## Rules

### Use the `color` prop for text color

```tsx
// ✅ Good
<Text color="labelPrimary">Hello</Text>
<Text color="labelSecondary">Subtitle</Text>
<Text color={isPositive ? "green" : "red"}>Amount</Text>

// ❌ Bad
<Text style={{ color: colors.labelPrimary }}>Hello</Text>
<Text style={{ ...typography.bodyRegular, color: colors.labelSecondary }}>Subtitle</Text>
```

### Use the `variant` prop for typography

```tsx
// ✅ Good
<Text variant="bodyRegular">Body text</Text>
<Text variant="title3Emphasized">Title</Text>
<Text variant="caption1Regular" color="labelSecondary">Caption</Text>

// ❌ Bad
<Text style={{ ...typography.bodyRegular }}>Body text</Text>
<Text style={{ ...typography.title3Emphasized, color: colors.labelPrimary }}>Title</Text>
```

### The `style` prop should only be used for layout properties

The `style` prop is acceptable for:
- `textAlign`
- `marginTop`, `marginBottom`, `margin`
- `paddingHorizontal`, `paddingVertical`, `padding`
- `textTransform`
- Custom font size overrides not in the typography tokens

```tsx
// ✅ Good - layout properties in style, color/variant as props
<Text variant="bodyRegular" color="labelSecondary" style={{ textAlign: "center" }}>
  Centered text
</Text>

<Text variant="caption1Emphasized" color="labelSecondary" style={{ textTransform: "uppercase" }}>
  SECTION HEADER
</Text>

// ✅ Good - custom sizing override (when token doesn't exist)
<Text variant="largeTitleEmphasized" style={{ fontSize: 48, lineHeight: 56 }}>
  $1,234.56
</Text>
```

## Available Props

- `color`: Any key from the `colors` token (e.g., `"labelPrimary"`, `"green"`, `"white"`)
- `variant`: Any key from the `typography` token (e.g., `"bodyRegular"`, `"title3Emphasized"`, `"caption1Regular"`)
